# BFF — Health Checks (M17-S04)
# /health/live is a pure process-up check — always 200, no dependencies.
# /health/ready checks the backend's /health/ready (2s timeout, chained — Cloud Run has no
# continuous readiness-based traffic pulling, only startup + liveness probes, so there's no
# cascading cost to checking the real dependency instead of just the backend's liveness) —
# 503 when the backend is unreachable or itself not ready (e.g. its DB is down).
# Both routes are @Public() (bypass JwtAuthGuard/TenantGuard/ActiveStaffGuard).

### GET /v1/health/live — always 200
GET {{bffUrl}}/v1/health/live

###

### GET /v1/health/ready — 200 when the backend is ready, 503 otherwise
GET {{bffUrl}}/v1/health/ready

###
